title: For Sale:  nightvision AN/PVS-15
postcontent:
I bought these from a buddy and they are awesome.  brand new they cost upwards of $12,000+ depending on where you get them.  these work great and are helmet mount ready.  I don't need them and am looking to get $6,000 obo and will trade for guns, gold, silver, cars, motorcycles etc.  let me know what you have.  five 41- 218 - 87five7 thanksThe AN/PVS-15 is based on the DoD nomenclature for the M953. It is a purpose-built ground operations binocular night vision device and is currently issued to members of USSOCOM. The AN/PVS-15 is self-contained, relatively lightweight unit that provides the operator with much-improved depth perception over single tube devices. The housing is engineered to be more rugged, yet still retain the same level of performance as aviation night vision goggles such as the ANVIS-9/6. The AN/PVS-15 is made by L3 Communications as a standard Gen3 Autogated configuration.
The AN/PVS-15 has been made famous by photos of USSOCOM operators wearing them in the Global War on Terror. They far surpass single tube systems when used in a land navigation or vehicle operation role. The human brain requires both eyes to determine depth. Using dual tubes, the brain can quickly and naturally resolve images.
The AN/PVS-15’s body housing is self contained and rugged. The battery compartment is part of the actual device, so there is no need to run a remote cable. Diopter and ocular adjustments are easy and familiar to anyone with NV experience. The tube housings are easily adjusted to fit the operator. The built-in IR Illuminator does a good job of lighting up close-in areas as well. Overall, the AN/PVS-15 is a very good piece of kit. In use with U.S. Military Tier1 groups, it sets the bar for binocular night vision devices.
